snippet.textDisplay: Quick Correction: Falcon Heavy has 4 major components (excluding the payload). The two side as well as the center core booster, all 3 of which are intended for landing and reuse. The 4th component is the 2nd stage which is required to raise the apogee of the launch trajectory to it's target height after the core booster decoupled. It is not capable of surviving reentry and burns up in the atmosphere and is therefor expendable. So not "all 3" parts land back on earth. I'm too much of a rocket nerd to not correct that ;)
